        <div class="item-head"><span class="item-title">Rushed Project Manager hire</span><span class="pill pill-yellow">Severity: Medium</span></div>
        <div class="item-body">Time pressure to "move fast" risks a hire that doesn't fit the "lean, scrappy" culture Whitney wants. <b>Mitigation:</b> use Andrew as interim PM while running a proper search in parallel.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="item-card">
        <div class="item-head"><span class="item-title">Promotions compress gross margin</span><span class="pill pill-yellow">Severity: Medium</span></div>
        <div class="item-body">DWB's 87% gross margin is a genuine asset; discount-heavy mechanics could erode it. <b>Mitigation:</b> model margin impact before finalizing discount depth; favor bundles/gifts-with-purchase.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="item-card">
        <div class="item-head"><span class="item-title">Overreacting to early Reddit sentiment</span><span class="pill pill-yellow">Severity: Medium</span></div>
        <div class="item-body">A handful of vocal posts could be mistaken for a broader trend. <b>Mitigation:</b> treat the first pass strictly as a baseline/listening exercise, not a trigger for response actions.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="item-card">
        <div class="item-head"><span class="item-title">Creative consolidation loses specialist depth</span><span class="pill pill-yellow">Severity: Medium</span></div>
        <div class="item-body">Combining photo/video/graphics into fewer roles risks losing a specialist's eye for high-stakes work (investor materials, TV segments). <b>Mitigation:</b> pilot one combined role before fully consolidating; keep a specialist bench.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============ FINAL RECOMMENDATIONS ============ -->
    <section class="page" id="final-recs">
      <div class="page-top">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">12 · Opportunities &amp; Risks</span>
          <h1 class="page-title">Final Recommendations</h1>
          <p class="page-subhead">The condensed close-out — five outcomes to hold the team accountable to over the next 90 days.</p>
        </div>
        <span class="context-pill">Prepared for Whitney &amp; leadership</span>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <ul class="rec-list">
          <li><b>Unblock paid marketing now</b> — Meta access is the single lowest-effort, highest-priority-score fix available; resolve it this week, not this quarter.</li>
          <li><b>Put a Project Manager in place within 30 days</b> — nearly every other gap in this plan depends on it, and Andrew has already offered to bridge the gap in the interim.</li>
          <li><b>Give the website and ecommerce engine a real owner</b> — AOV and conversion rate are already improving; protect that trend before it stalls from lack of attention.</li>
          <li><b>Verify regulatory standing before the SAFE round closes</b> — a two-week runway doesn't guarantee full resolution, but it's enough time to know where DWB stands and say so to investors.</li>
          <li><b>Sequence deliberately</b> — hold channel diversification until the operational foundation (PM, ecommerce, creative) is in place; don't let ambition outrun the team's current capacity.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</div>

<script>
  const navItems = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-item');
  const pages = document.querySelectorAll('.page');
  navItems.forEach(item => {
    item.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const target = item.getAttribute('data-page');
      navItems.forEach(n => n.classList.remove('active'));
      item.classList.add('active');
      pages.forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));
      const el = document.getElementById(target);
      if (el) { el.classList.add('active'); }
      document.querySelector('.content').scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'instant'});
      window.scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'instant'});
    });
  });
</script>
